The term "'''Middle Australian'''" is a socio-political term which generally refers to [[middle class]] or [[lower-middle class]] Australian people who hold [[traditional conservative|traditional]] or [[right-wing politics|right-wing views]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/it-pro/racial-discrimination-backdown-a-triumph-of-middle-australian-values-20140807-101hve.html|title=Racial discrimination backdown a triumph of 'middle Australian' values|publisher= [[The Sydney Morning Herald|SMH]]|accessdate=December 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/federal-politics/political-opinion/the-big-question-for-2013-who-will-own-middle-australia-20121021-27zh5.html|title=The big question for 2013: who will 'own' middle Australia?|publisher= [[The Sydney Morning Herald|SMH]]|accessdate=December 29, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessspectator.com.au/article/2011/5/16/interest-rates/middle-australia-suffering|title=Middle Australia is suffering|publisher=[[Business Spectator]]|accessdate=December 29, 2014}}</ref> As such, it does not refer to the [[Central Australia|geographical middle]] of the country, by rather to the socio-economic middle (as is also the primary meaning of the monikers "[[Middle America (United States)|Middle America]]" or "[[Middle England]]").<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=_7TThWTP6N0C&pg=PA96&lpg=PA96&dq=middle+australia+is+suffering&source=bl&ots=T6cmYkCFpE&sig=XiKHyygr0UwxEUntNcdpl2Ejwww&hl=en&sa=X&ei=M5ugVJrLIMyuU-vKg7gL&ved=0CCgQ6AEwATgK#v=onepage&q=middle%20australia%20is%20suffering&f=false|title=Inequality in Australia|publisher=Books.google.co.uk|accessdate=29 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=njUwmzqaN8QC&pg=PA138&lpg=PA138&dq=middle+australia+politics&source=bl&ots=Hx3HoGXS5V&sig=9vuDcKNlIk2qgcCTJHIJGJsbSx0&hl=en&sa=X&ei=X5qgVKSUEubO7ga_gIHgDg&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=middle%20australia%20politics&f=false|title=The Experience of Middle Australia|publisher=Books.google.co.uk|accessdate=29 December 2014}}</ref> 


