'''Sierra Leonean English''' is the [[List of dialects of the English language|dialect of English]] spoken by [[Sierra Leonean]]s which has been heavily influenced by the [[Sierra Leone Creole people]].

==Pronunciation==
Sierra Leonean English realizes {{IPA|/r/}} as a [[voiced uvular fricative]], or, more rarely, a [[uvular trill]].{{sfnp|Ladefoged|Maddieson|1996|p=236}} This is rare among accents of English.{{sfnp|Collins|Mees|2013|p=199}}

==See also==
* [[Krio language]], an English-based creole language originally spoken by the [[Krio people]] in Sierra Leone and today the country's main lingua franca.

